start_time), we are prioritizing non-Monday.\n    # But the instruction says "Find the earliest... Among multiple valid options, prefer...".\n    # This usually means:\n    # 1. Find the minimum start_time.\n    # 2. If there are multiple slots with that same minimum start_time, use preferences.\n    # Since we have minute granularity, there\'s only one slot with the minimum start_time.\n    # UNLESS "multiple valid options" means "all valid options".\n    # If it means "all valid options", then the instruction is:\n    # Sort by (is_monday, start_time).\n    # Let\'s try sorting by (is_monday, start_time) and see if it works.\n    # Wait, if I sort by (is_monday, start_time), I\'m saying "Give me the earliest non-Monday slot".\n    # That\'s a common interpretation of "prefer".\n    \n    valid_slots.sort(key=lambda x: (1 if x[\'is_monday\'] else 0, x[\'start\']))\n    return valid_slots[0]\n\nresult = solve()\nif result:\n    print(f"START:{result[\'start\'].strftime(\'%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ\')}")\n    print(f"END:{result[\'end\'].strftime(\'%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ\')}")\nelse:\n    print("NONE")\nEOF\npython3 /app/solver.py\n'})
